<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Angels Cut O'Brien </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- The Anaheim Angels designated catcher  
Charlie O'Brien for assignment on Monday and called up catcher Ben 
Molina from Triple-A Edmonton. 
</P>
<P>
	O'Brien, who spent seven weeks on the disabled list because of a  
torn ligament in his right foot, had only six hits in 62 at-bats 
this season while playing in 27 games. 
</P>
<P>
	The 12-year veteran has played for seven major league teams  
since 1985, batting .221 with 55 home runs, and played with the 
World Series champion Atlanta Braves in 1995. 
</P>
<P>
	Molina, 25, played 65 games for Edmonton this season and batted  
.286 with seven homers and 41 RBIs. He appeared in two games last 
season for the Angels, who originally signed him as a free agent in 
May 1993. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
