<HEADLINE> Delta Makes Emergency Landing in NY </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A Delta Air Lines plane made an emergency  
landing today at Kennedy Airport after the pilot reported smoke in 
the cabin shortly after takeoff from nearby LaGuardia Airport. 
</P>
<P>
	More than 100 passengers aboard Flight 305 bound for Atlanta  
were evacuated, said Port Authority spokesman Greg Trevor. No 
injuries were immediately reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The smoke was reported shortly after the plane took off around 8  
a.m. Port Authority police at Kennedy reported seeing a flame 
shooting from one engine as the plane landed but there was no fire 
in the cabin, Trevor said. 
</P>
<P>
	Emergency equipment was standing by when the plane landed and  
chutes were deployed, Trevor said. 
</P>
<P>
	The cause of the problem was under investigation.  

  	   	
</P>
