<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 'Runaway Bride' Debuts at $35.1M / Box Office  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Julia Roberts and Richard Gere's reunion  
lovefest ``Runaway Bride'' ran away with the record for a romantic 
comedy debut and outpaced a trio of horror films over the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	``Runaway Bride'' led the box office with $35.1 million, easily  
beating the scary ``The Blair Witch Project,'' the shark-infested 
``Deep Blue Sea'' and the spooky ``The Haunting.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The previous record for a romance romp was $27.7 million over  
Memorial Day weekend by ``Notting Hill,'' also starring Roberts, 
whose career began soaring when she paired with Gere in 1990's 
``Pretty Woman.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The top 20 movies at North American theaters Friday through  
Sunday, followed by distributing studio, gross, number of theater 
locations, average receipts per location, total gross and number of 
weeks in release, as compiled Monday by Exhibitor Relations Co. 
Inc. and ACNielsen EDI Inc. 
</P>
<P>
	1. ``Runaway Bride,'' Paramount, $35.1 million, 3,158 locations,  
$11,101 average, $35.1 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	2. ``The Blair Witch Project,'' Artisan, $29.2 million, 1,101  
locations, $26,528 average, $36.1 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	3. ``Deep Blue Sea,'' Warner Bros., $19.1 million, 2,854  
locations, $6,695 average, $25.2 million, one week. 
</P>
<P>
	4. ``The Haunting,'' DreamWorks, $15.3 million, 2,864 locations,  
$5,327 average, $64 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	5. ``Inspector Gadget,'' Disney, $14.1 million, 2,877 locations,  
$4,912 average, $47.9 million, two weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	6. ``American Pie,'' Universal, $6.8 million, 2,436 locations,  
$2,785 average, $77.2 million, four weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	7. ``Eyes Wide Shut,'' Warner Bros., $4.3 million, 2,264  
locations, $1,908 average, $48.7 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	8. ``Big Daddy,'' Sony, $3.6 million, 2,288 locations, $1,555  
average, $152.7 million, six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	9. ``Star Wars: Episode I -- The Phantom Menace,'' 20th Century  
Fox, $3.4 million, 1,628 locations, $2,101 average, $408.6 million, 
11 weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	10. ``Tarzan,'' Disney, $3 million, 1,611 locations, $1,884  
average, $158.4 million, seven weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	11. ``Lake Placid,'' 20th Century Fox, $2.7 million, 1,798  
locations, $1,490 average, $26.6 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	12. ``The Wood,'' Paramount, $2.6 million, 1,052 locations,  
$2,444 average, $20.6 million, three weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	13. ``Wild Wild West,'' Warner Bros., $2.5 million, 2,151  
locations, $1,164 average, $108.9 million, five weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	14. ``The General's Daughter,'' Paramount, $2.3 million, 1,319  
locations, $1,732 average, $97.8 million, seven weeks. 
</P>
