<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Partly cloudy skies and dry conditions were seen across much of  
the eastern third of the country on Tuesday. Showers were seen in 
parts of the West. 
</P>
<P>
	Scattered clouds were seen from the Northeast, south across the  
Ohio Valley, the Mid-Atlantic region, and into the Southeast. 
</P>
<P>
	Some showers and thunderstorms were seen off of the Mid-Atlantic  
coast and west of Florida in the Gulf of Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	A developing area of low pressure combined with a stationary  
front to bring rain showers to parts of the central Plains. 
</P>
<P>
	Monsoonal flow continue to feed moisture into the  
Desert-Southwest and the Rockies. Scattered showers and 
thunderstorms were seen from the northern Rockies of Montana and 
Idaho, south into the Desert Southwest. The heaviest activity is 
being detected by radar over eastern Arizona and New Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 39 in  
Whitefield, N.H., to an early-afternoon high of 97 in Biloxi, Miss. 
With the heat index, it felt like 119 in Biloxi. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
