<HEADLINE> Singer Barry White Hospitalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Barry White is in the hospital for a  
blood pressure problem, forcing him and Earth, Wind &AMP; Fire to 
cancel several shows. 
</P>
<P>
	Promoter Jeff Sharp wouldn't provide further details Tuesday.  
</P>
<P>
	A written statement issued by the Nashville Arena announcing the  
cancellation of the Aug. 14 White-Earth, Wind &AMP; Fire concert said 
the romantic signer is suffering from exhaustion. 
</P>
<P>
	Concerts in New Orleans, Dallas and Detroit were also canceled.  
</P>
<P>
	White, perhaps best known lately for his cameo appearances on  
the television show ``Ally McBeal,'' had several hits in the 
mid-1970s, including ``Can't Get Enough of Your Love, Babe.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
