<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Cubans Beat U.S. for Baseball Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WINNIPEG, Manitoba (AP) -- The Cubans came to the top of their  
dugout steps in the top of the ninth, dancing to a drum beat in the 
stands, ready to unfurl four of their nation's flags, ready to 
celebrate yet another baseball championship. 
</P>
<P>
	When a 5-1 victory over the United States was secured, so was  
the gold medal in the Pan American Games, and the Cubans rushed the 
field in jubilation. 
</P>
<P>
	They were able to overcome any distractions caused by numerous  
defections from their athletic teams, including one of their own, 
relief pitcher Danys Baez after Sunday's semifinal win over Canada. 
</P>
<P>
	``The Cuban team is a very good, but not an unbeatable team by  
any means. It's disappointing, but we accomplished a lot here,'' 
said U.S. manager Buddy Bell, whose hastily assembled team clinched 
an Olympic berth the night before by beating Mexico in the 
semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
	Cuba got two homers from long-ball star Orestes Kindelan -- the  
career home run leader in the country's history with 430 before the 
tourament -- and an overpowering pitching performance by Jose 
Contreras on one day's rest. 
</P>
<P>
	``We can't communicate with them all that well, but they  
conducted themselves professionally,'' U.S. third baseman Jason 
Hardtke said. ``They were the team to beat. We beat them once, but 
then we came up short.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Kindelan was 3-for-25 in the tournament before hitting a two-out  
homer in the fourth off starter Brad Penny for a 1-0 lead. The next 
batter, Gabriel Pierre, followed with another homer. 
</P>
<P>
	Kindelan homered again, a two-run shot, in the sixth. And the  
United States could manage just one run on a double by Milton 
Bradley and RBI single by Marcus Jensen. 
</P>
<P>
	Contreras, who pitched six innings in a quarterfinal win over  
the Dominican Rebublic, struck out 13 in eight innings, including 
eight straight early in the game. The Cubans won their eighth 
straight Pan Ams gold. 
</P>
<P>
	``He is their best pitcher,'' Bell said. ``The guy is a horse,  
too, but he can't do that all the time -- or he shouldn't be able 
to. 
</P>
<P>
	``Obviously, they don't care about anybody's health over there,  
which is a shame.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The United States beat Cuba in the preliminary rounds 10-5.  
Canada also defeated the Cubans in the round robin before losing in 
the semifinals. Canada, despite the best record in the tournament, 
6-1, got only a bronze medal and no trip to the Olympics. The 
Canadians beat Mexico 9-2 Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Off the field, Cuba's problems mounted. Cuban officials  
denounced organizers for lax security that led to defections and 
disappearances that have plagued the team. They also criticized 
officials for failing to stop a demonstrator from disrupting 
Sunday's semifinal victory over Canada. 
</P>
<P>
	When the 19-year-old Baez left the team, telling a Miami  
television station he was headed for south Florida, the Cubans 
insisted that organizers tighten security. 
</P>
<P>
	``Cuban athletes will not permit anyone or anything to humiliate  
them ... if their dignity is at stake,'' a statement from the Cuban 
delegation said. ``From now on we will react with full energy to 
provocations.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Sports agent Joe Cubas, who has helped many Cubans defect to the  
United States, said in a release Monday that Baez sought asylum in 
Canada after the semifinal win. Baez told Miami television station 
WSCV 51 via telephone, ``I want to tell the people of Miami that 
another Cuban in search of freedom is about to become part of the 
people of Miami. Wait for me over there.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Baez's departure brought to eight the number of Cubans to leave  
during the games. Runner Michal Ortiz, an unidentified female 
artistic gymnast and a soccer goalkeeper -- the goalies here were 
Rene Castro and Rodney Valdes -- also left the team on the weekend. 
</P>
<P>
	Canadian roller hockey goalkeeper Steve Vezina apologized for  
testing positive for three banned substances, costing his team a 
gold medal. At a news conference in Saint-Adele, Quebec, Vezina 
said, ``Those actions were not up to a high standard of an athlete 
that represents Canada.'' 
</P>
<P>
	That didn't soothe teammate Kevin Kerr.  
</P>
<P>
	``He ruined the chance of a lifetime for nine guys,'' Kerr said.  
``I know he's my teammate and I should be sticking up for him. I 
know I, along with nine other guys, we're clean. We did it the way 
we were supposed to do it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Juana Rosario of the Dominican Republic, winner of the women's  
high jump, failed her drug test, a games officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
	Cuba's men's volleyball team beat Brazil in five sets for the  
gold medal. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. team closed in on 200 medals, upping its total to 188,  
74 gold. Canada is next at 111, 33 gold, followed by Cuba with 96, 
39 gold. 
</P>
<P>
	The American women's soccer team advanced to the gold medal game  
by beating Costa Rica 2-0. Marcia Wallis and Kim Patrick scored for 
the Americans, who outshot Costa Rica 22-0 in the second half and 
34-1 for the game. 
</P>
<P>
	Mexico beat Canada in a shootout for the other spot in the  
finals. 
</P>
<P>
	Teen-age tennis star Alexandra Stevenson got her first test,  
needing a third-set tiebreaker to edge Renata Kolbovic of Canada 
7-6 (9-7), 4-6, 7-6 (7-4). 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. women played their best basketball game so far, but  
couldn't hold a 16-point lead and lost to Brazil 77-72. 
</P>
<P>
	Americans collected one gold, by Ed Moses in the 100-meter  
breaststroke in games record time (1:00.99), and four silvers in 
swimming. 
</P>
<P>
	Today, the U.S. swim team was assured of not collecting a medal  
in an individual event for the first time since 1955 when Jarod 
Schroeder and Sabir Muhammad failed to qualify for the final of the 
men's 100 butterfly. Schroeder finished 11th overall in the 
preliminaries at 55.89 and Muhammad was 17th at 57.20. Only the top 
eight make the final. 
</P>
<P>
	In beating Chile 2-0, the U.S. women's field hockey team made  
the final game. If it wins that over Argentina, it goes to the 
Sydney Games. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
