<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily Tuesday on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *UnumProvident Corp., down 15 5/16 at 36 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The insurance company lost 80 cents per share in the second  
quarter, compared to a profit of 71 cents per share in last year's 
second quarter. The company attributed the loss to merger costs and 
an early retirement offer to employees. 

</P>
<P>
 *National Discount Brokers, down 4 15/16 at 32 1/8  
</P>
<P>
 *Charles Schwab Corp., down 4 11/16 at 37 3/4 
</P>
<P>
	Bill Burnham, Internet analyst at Credit Suisse First Boston,  
said online brokerage firms experienced weak trading volumes in 
July, and may see their first-ever decline in trading volume in the 
third quarter. 

</P>
<P>
 *Federal-Mogul Corp., down 2 1/8 at 46 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Federal-Mogul, a Southfield, Mich., maker of auto parts, will  
acquire Sabo Industria e Comercio Ltda., a Brazilian maker of 
gaskets, seals and hoses. The purchase price was not disclosed. 

</P>
<P>
 *Waste Management Inc., down 1 1/4 at 24 3/16    	
</P>
<P>
	After lowering its own earnings forecasts twice, Waste  
Management posted profits that came in at the low end of estimates. 
The company has blamed poor forecasting and lower-than-expected 
trash collection revenues. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Henry Schein Inc., down 5 3/8 at 15 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The health product distributor said the integration of H. Meer  
Dental Supply resulted in lower-than-expected second quarter dental 
sales of $261 million, 8 percent below year-ago figures. Schein 
also said dental sales will be weak in the third quarter. 

</P>
<P>
 *Provident Financial Group Inc., up 1/16 at 43 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Provident and OHSL Financial Corp. of Cincinnati will merge in a  
stock swap. Under terms of the agreement, OHSL shareholders will 
receive Provident common shares valued at $57 million. 

</P>
<P>
 *Algos Pharmaceutical Corp., down 14 5/16 at 9 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Neptune, N.J.-based, pharmaceutical company received a ``not  
approvable'' letter from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration 
regarding MorphiDex, Algos's proposed treatment for moderate to 
severe pain from cancer. 

</P>
<P>
 *Radiant Systems Inc., up 3 3/16 at 19 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	America Online Inc. and Radiant will develop a service that will  
allow consumers to receive e-mail, news and other information at 
stores and restaurants. As part of the deal, AOL will make an 
investment in Radiant, a maker of computerized payment systems. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
