<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Adult Film Stars Sue Charlie Sheen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Two adult film stars have filed a lawsuit  
against Charlie Sheen and his bodyguard for an alleged assault at 
the movie star's home. 
</P>
<P>
	Erin Siemen, whose stage name is Charlisse L'Amour, and  
Christina Lee Stramaglia, who performs as Teri Star, contend they 
were roughed up by Curtis Hunt on July 26 after they arrived at the 
door of Sheen's home. 
</P>
<P>
	Miss Sieman alleges that she was summoned to the home by Sheen,  
but when she and Miss Stramaglia arrived, there was no response. 
</P>
<P>
	She then hopped over the fence and was punched in the face by  
Hunt, the lawsuit alleges. Miss Stramaglia said she was also 
assaulted by Hunt after hopping the fence. 
</P>
<P>
	The actor's attorney, Zia Modabber, called the lawsuit  
``completely frivolous'' on Tuesday. Modabber said they filed the 
suit Friday after Sheen obtained a restraining order against them 
last Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	``Mr. Sheen and Mr. Hunt strongly deny these allegations and  
plan to vigorously defend themselves in court,'' Modabber said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
