also said dental sales will be weak in the third quarter. 

</P>
<P>
 *Provident Financial Group Inc., up 1/8 at 43 3/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Provident and OHSL Financial Corp. of Cincinnati will merge in a  
stock swap. Under terms of the agreement, OHSL shareholders will 
receive Provident common shares valued at $57 million. 

</P>
<P>
 *Algos Pharmaceutical Corp., down 14 7/16 at 9 13/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Neptune, N.J.-based, pharmaceutical company received a ``not  
approvable'' letter from the U.S. Food and Drug Administration 
regarding MorphiDex, Algos's proposed treatment for moderate to 
severe pain from cancer. 

</P>
<P>
 *Radiant Systems Inc., up 3 9/16 at 19 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	America Online Inc. and Radiant will develop a service that will  
allow consumers to receive e-mail, news and other information at 
stores and restaurants. As part of the deal, AOL will make an 
investment in Radiant, a maker of computerized payment systems. 


  	   	
</P>
