<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Michael Douglas Is Still Not Engaged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Michael Douglas and Catherine Zeta-Jones are  
dating but they aren't engaged to marry -- yet. 
</P>
<P>
	A London tabloid reported this week that an engagement party is  
planned for Sept. 25, but Douglas publicist Allen Burry said 
Tuesday the newspaper apparently confused information about a joint 
birthday party planned that day. 
</P>
<P>
	``They took it another step and made more out of it than there  
really is,'' Burry said, adding the couple was indeed ``an item'' 
and that they ``do date.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Both actors' birthday is Sept. 25. Every year, Douglas has a  
party with people who share his birthday, including Barbara Walters 
and Christopher Reeve. 
</P>
<P>
	``Last year, when they found out Catherine also shared the  
birthday, they invited her to the party but she was filming and 
couldn't make it,'' Burry said. ``This year, she's going.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Asked whether an engagement announcement was possible at that  
time, Burry said, ``Well, September's a long way away.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
