<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Six Die in Big-Rig Desert Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BORON, Calif. (AP) -- Six people, including a family of four,  
were killed when three 7 1/2-ton concrete pipes fell from a truck and 
crushed two vehicles along a desert highway. 
</P>
<P>
	Trucker Richard Sommerville, 59, was booked for investigation of  
drunken driving shortly after the accident early Monday on Highway 
58, California Highway Patrol Officer Todd Weichers said. 
Sommerville was not hurt. 
</P>
<P>
	A family of four from Redlands was killed when their minivan  
struck the rolling pipes, police reported. A man and woman in a 
Chevrolet were also killed. 
</P>
<P>
	Traffic was diverted around the site about 75 miles north of Los  
Angeles near Edwards Air Force Base. 
</P>
<P>
	Sommerville's truck was traveling west, pulling a flatbed  
trailer with the pipes when he entered a curve and straps 
restraining three concrete pipes weighing 15,000 pounds each 
snapped. The pipes were 30 feet long and 3 feet wide. 
</P>
<P>
	``The pipes fell off the trailer and became airborne,'' Weichers  
said. 
</P>
<P>
	Two vehicles in the eastbound lanes of the highway were struck  
by the pipes, killing all six occupants ``in a heartbeat,'' 
Weichers said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
