<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jagger Hailed As 'Loving' Father </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The mother of Mick Jagger's newest child praises  
the rock star as a ``very loving father'' -- even though he has yet 
to meet the 4-month-old boy. 
</P>
<P>
	In an interview with Hello! magazine, Brazilian model Luciana  
Morad spoke about her relationship with the Rolling Stones' lead 
singer and posed for photos with baby Lucas. 
</P>
<P>
	British news reports said Ms. Morad's pregnancy was the last  
straw for Jerry Hall, who recently separated from Jagger after 22 
years for a reported multimillion-dollar settlement. 
</P>
<P>
	``Mick is a very decent man and he loves all his children. He  
does not blame Lucas for being born,'' said Ms. Morad, 29. ``He is 
a very loving father and, as fathers go, Lucas couldn't be 
luckier.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Results of a blood test last month proved Jagger was Lucas'  
father. Ms. Morad said the Stones' hectic world tour has so far 
prevented him from seeing his new son. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
