<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 08:30:26 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Turn Mixed; Dow Up 43.70 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks turned mixed today after a strong opening  
as interest rate concerns kept investors on edge. 
</P>
<P>
	At 11 a.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
up 43.70 at 10,689.66. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mostly lower after giving up early  
gains. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was up 0.04 at 1,328.09, and 
the Nasdaq composite index was down 16.84 at 2,606.79. 
</P>
<P>
	Concerns that the Federal Reserve will raise rates later this  
month in an effort to cool off the economy held most stocks back. 
The Conference Board provided the latest hint that the nation's 
unbridled economic growth is continuing, announcing that its index 
of leading indicators rose 0.3 percent in June, matching its May 
increase. The index is used to forecast economic trends for the 
coming three to six months. 
</P>
<P>
	A report that ExciteAtHome may be acquired by Yahoo! for a price  
greater than ExciteAtHome's $17 billion market value stimulated 
some early buying in Internet and telecommunications companies. 
Shares of ExciteAtHome rose sharply, only to slip back when the 
company's chief executive officer denied the rumors. ExciteAtHome 
was up just 1/2 at 43 7/16. 
</P>
<P>
	Meanwhile, Bill Burnham, an Internet analyst at Credit Suisse  
First Boston, said in a report that online brokerages may 
experience their first ever decline in trading volume in the third 
quarter. Shares of ETrade fell 3 9/16 to 25 7/16, and Charles 
Schwab fell 3 15/16 to 38 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
	Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a 3-to-2 margin on the  
New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 223.26 million 
shares, ahead of Monday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was down 0.68 at 624.66, and the  
American Stock Exchange composite index was up 1.28 at 785.92. 
</P>
<P>
	The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies was down 3.91 at  
438.72. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
