<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Green Bay Re-Signs Hollinquest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GREEN BAY, Wis. (AP) -- Lamont Hollinquest was back with the  
Green Bay Packers on Tuesday, though he wasn't quite sure why. 
</P>
<P>
	Hollinquest, a special-teams standout and backup linebacker the  
last three seasons with the Packers, wanted a chance to be a 
defensive starter. He thought he'd get it when he signed a 
two-year, $1.6 million contract with the Kansas City Chiefs on 
March 5. 
</P>
<P>
	He participated in Kansas City's minicamps during the summer and  
was looking forward to training camp. But on July 21, the Chiefs 
abruptly waived him. 
</P>
<P>
	Hollinquest was informed of the decision by a letter in the  
mail. 
</P>
<P>
	``They never told me specifically (why),'' he said. ``There were  
some things they were going through. I'm not mad at them. They did 
what they thought was best for their team.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Chiefs director of pro personnel John Schneider did not return a  
phone call Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	With the openings of most NFL training camps only days away,  
Hollinquest was out of work. His agent, Gary Uberstine, contacted 
the Packers, who said they didn't have the salary cap room. 
</P>
<P>
	But that changed when wide receiver Robert Brooks announced his  
retirement on Monday. The Packers were then able pick up 
Hollinquest, in part with the $700,000 of extra salary cap room 
Brooks' departure created. 
</P>
<P>
	Hollinquest is the second former Chiefs linebacker signed by the  
Packers within a week. Green Bay picked up Anthony Davis on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Packers will take all the depth they can get at the  
position. Jude Waddy, expected to be a key performer for the team, 
will miss the first two games of the regular season while 
completing a suspension for steroid use. 
</P>
<P>
	Green Bay likes Hollinquest's ability to play all three  
linebacker positions. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've got some quality players at linebacker, but it's always  
good to have extra people for matchups and injuries,'' defensive 
coordinator Emmitt Thomas said. ``The more looks you can put out on 
the field, the better.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Hollinquest played three seasons with Green Bay and also has  
played for Washington and Cincinnati. He worked with Thomas when 
both were with the Redskins. 
</P>
<P>
	Hollinquest started two games at right outside linebacker for  
the Packers last season while George Koonce was sidelined with a 
hamstring injury. He made 13 tackles at linebacker last season and 
a team-best eight on special teams. 
</P>
<P>
	``I should have never left,'' Hollinquest said. ``I had a solid  
foundation with the players and all my friends. I thought the 
opportunity was elsewhere, but it didn't turn out that way.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
