<HEADLINE> Islanders' Potvin Signs for 1 Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	UNIONDALE, N.Y. (AP) -- Goalie Felix Potvin didn't get a raise  
when he signed a one-year contract with the New York Islanders. The 
way things went for him last season, though, he said he didn't 
expect one. 
</P>
<P>
	``Just knowing that I'm going to camp and playing, I'm happy, ''  
Potvin said Monday after signing for $2.7 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season was not particularly noteworthy for the 28-year-old  
Potvin. It began with a long holdout with the Toronto Maple Leafs. 
And, then after appearing in only five games, he was traded in 
January to the Islanders, he was bothered by a nagging groin 
injury. He was 2-7-1 with the Islanders and had a 3.66 goals 
against average. 
</P>
<P>
	The highlight of his season was a 55-saves game against the New  
Jersey Devils in April. 
</P>
