</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Former NBA great Isiah Thomas is paying $10  
million for the nine CBA franchises and plans to reorganize the 
league into a single entity. The CBA will control operation of each 
team. Thomas wants to expand the developmental basketball league 
into NBA affiliations. 

</P>
<P>
	AP NewsBrief by HOWARD SINER  
  	   	
