<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Tim McGraw Leads CMA Nominations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Tim McGraw was nominated for seven  
Country Music Association awards today, and will compete with 1998 
winner Garth Brooks for the top award of best entertainer. 
</P>
<P>
	McGraw's other nominations were for best male vocalist, album  
(``A Place in the Sun''), single (``Please Remember Me'') and music 
video (``Just to Hear You Say That You Love Me''). He'll get two 
trophies if he wins the best album or single awards, as a producer. 
</P>
<P>
	Singers Brenda Lee, Sherrie Austin and Brad Paisley announced  
the nominees in the courtyard of the Grand Ole Opry House. The 
winners will be revealed inside the building Sept. 22 during a 
ceremony broadcast live on CBS-TV. 
</P>
<P>
	Vince Gill, the most awarded performer in CMA history with 17,  
will host the show for the eighth straight year. He got five 
nominations: best male vocalist, album (``The Key''), song (``If 
You Ever Have Forever in Mind'') and two nods for best vocal event 
for duets with Patty Loveless and Sara Evans. 
</P>
<P>
	Nominees for best entertainer along with Brooks and McGraw were  
George Strait, Shania Twain and the Dixie Chicks. Joining McGraw 
and Gill in the best male vocalist category were Strait, Alan 
Jackson and Steve Wariner. 
</P>
<P>
	Best female vocalist nominees were Twain, Faith Hill, Martina  
McBride, Jo Dee Messina and Trisha Yearwood. 
</P>
<P>
	``This year's list of CMA nominees consists of an eclectic mix  
of country music luminaries and exciting new talent,'' said Ed 
Benson, executive director of the CMA. 
</P>
<P>
	The most notable breakthrough was that of the female trio the  
Dixie Chicks -- Natalie Maines and sisters Martie Siedel and Emily 
Erwin. Along with the best entertainer nomination, the group's 
``Wide Open Spaces'' is up for best single and video. They'll also 
compete with Alabama, Diamond Rio, Lonestar and The Wilkinsons for 
best vocal group. 
</P>
<P>
	Late country music singer Roger Miller was nominated for best  
song for his 1966 hit ``Husbands and Wives,'' which was returned to 
the charts by Brooks &AMP; Dunn. George Jones continued his comeback 
from a near-fatal car wreck with a nomination for best single for 
``Choices.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Pop singer Linda Ronstadt was nominated for best vocal event  
along with Dolly Parton and Emmylou Harris for their ``Trio II'' 
album. Parton will be inducted into the Country Music Hall of Fame 
during the awards show, along with late singers Conway Twitty and 
Johnny Bond. 
</P>
<P>
	About 6,800 workers in the country music industry nominate and  
vote for CMA winners. The CMA awards began in 1967. 
</P>
<P>
	------	 
</P>
<P>
	Finalists for 1999 Country Music Association awards. Winners  
will be announced Sept. 22 at the Grand Ole Opry House. 

</P>
