<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Storm Hooks Up With Lightning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) -- The Toledo Storm of the East Coast Hockey  
League announced it will become an affiliate of the Tampa Bay 
Lightning next season. 
</P>
<P>
	The Storm will serve as the Double-A farm team for Tampa's top  
minor league team, the Detroit Vipers. 
</P>
<P>
	The club also announced Monday that Todd Gordon would take over  
as coach. Gordon, 32, played in the ECHL and coached last season 
with the San Antonio Iguanas of the Central Hockey League. 
</P>
<P>
	The Storm ended its affiliation with the Detroit Red Wings this  
year when Detroit announced it was moving its top minor league team 
to a new arena in suburban Toledo. 
</P>
<P>
	The Red Wings' American Hockey League team will begin playing at  
the $48 million arena next year in Rossford. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
