<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Anwar Lawyers Threaten To Impeach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) -- Defense lawyers in the sodomy  
trial of Malaysia's ousted deputy prime minister threatened today 
to impeach the prosecution's star witness. 
</P>
<P>
	Defense attorney Christopher Fernando told the judge that Anwar  
Ibrahim's former family driver, Azizan Abu Bakar -- who accused his 
ex-boss of sodomizing him several times in 1992 and 1993 -- lacked 
credibility as a witness. 
</P>
<P>
	``I will show that this man was made use of and his evidence is  
fabricated,'' Fernando told High Court Judge Ariffin Jaka. ``I am 
laying the foundation with a view to impeach him if necessary.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Azizan, who has been on the witness stand since last Wednesday,  
has accused Anwar and his adopted brother Sukma Dermawan of 
sodomizing him up to 15 times in different locations. His testimony 
last week was closed to the media and the public, but recorded on 
videotape. 
</P>
<P>
	The defense also threatened to prosecute Azizan for perjury  
during Anwar's first trial last November. Anwar was convicted of 
abusing power and is serving a six-year jail term. 
</P>
<P>
	Anwar says the charges were fabricated to end his challenge to  
Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad. 
</P>
<P>
	Sodomy is a crime in predominantly Muslim Malaysia, punishable  
by 20 years in prison and a whipping. Anwar's adopted brother is 
also on trial. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
