<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 61; Nasdaq Is Up 24 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 61 points  
in today's early going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange 
hold a 3-2 lead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up 24 points and the S&AMP;P 500 Index  
is up six points. 
</P>
<P>
	The high-tech sector is likely to draw strength today from a  
report that Yahoo! has been holding merger talks with 
Excite/AtHome. 
</P>
<P>
	But market-watchers says Wall Street is increasingly likely to  
trade cautiously as we move closer to the Federal Reserve's next 
policy meeting. 
</P>
<P>
	The central bank is scheduled to meet about interest rates three  
weeks from today. 
</P>
<P>
	As a result, concerns about interest rates are leading to more  
negative reactions to economic data. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow, for instance, posted solid early gains yesterday, only  
to surrender the move by the closing bell. 
</P>
<P>
	This morning, the Conference Board is due to release its June  
index of Leading Indicators. 
</P>
<P>
	Bond prices have been narrowly lower ahead of the report.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
