<DOCNO> APW19990803.0327 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-03 08:40:28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Son of Homeless Woman Sues L.A. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The son of a homeless woman fatally shot  
after allegedly threatening a policeman with a screwdriver is suing 
the city and police department. 
</P>
<P>
	Richard Mitchell's civil rights lawsuit filed Monday in federal  
court contends that his frail, mentally ill mother posed no threat 
to the officers when she was killed May 21. 
</P>
<P>
	Margaret Mitchell, 54, had been pushing a shopping cart down  
trendy La Brea Avenue when two officers stopped her and asked if 
the cart was stolen. Police said the woman then thrust a 
screwdriver at one of the officers, who fell to one knee and fired 
a shot into her chest. 
</P>
<P>
	The officer was not injured. Ms. Mitchell died later at a  
hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	The suit accuses the police department of assault, battery and  
wrongful death and claims the city was negligent in hiring the two 
officers. Named in the suit are Police Chief Bernard Parks and 
officers Edward Larrigan, 27, and Kathy Clark, 29. 
</P>
<P>
	Police officials declined to comment on the lawsuit Monday,  
citing the pending litigation. The city attorney had not yet seen 
the lawsuit and could not comment, a spokesman said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
