<HEADLINE> Clinton To Host Turkish Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton will meet here next month  
with the Turkish prime minister, Bulent Ecevit, the White House 
said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Ecevit will visit Sept. 28 follows a trip to Turkey last month  
by Defense Secretary William Cohen. Like that visit, Ecevit's 
meeting will include a discussion of Turkey's longstanding dispute 
with Greece over the island of Cyprus, National Security Council 
spokesman David Leavy said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Resolving Cyprus is a key priority for the administration,''  
Leavy said. 
</P>
<P>
	The United States is encouraged by both sides' willingness to  
hold negotiations this fall, Leavy said. 
</P>
<P>
	Turkey invaded Cyprus in 1974 after an Athens-backed coup on the  
island by supporters of union with Greece. Turkish troops are still 
stationed in a Turkish-Cypriot enclave on the island. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
