<HEADLINE> Braves Place Otis Nixon on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Outfielder Otis Nixon was placed on the 15-day  
disabled list by the Atlanta Braves on Tuesday with a sprained 
neck. 
</P>
<P>
	The club said Nixon was injured during Friday night's fight with  
the Philadelphia Phillies. The trouble began when Atlanta catcher 
Eddie Perez, who had been hit by a Paul Byrd pitch earlier in the 
game, punched Byrd as the Phillies right-hander entered the batters 
box. 
</P>
<P>
	By placing Nixon on the DL retroactive to Thursday, the Braves  
made room on their roster for one of two players acquired in 
Saturday's trade with the Chicago Cubs. Atlanta sent left-hander 
Micah Bowie and two minor leaguers to the Cubs for 
infielder-outfielder Jose Hernandez and pitcher Terry Mulholland. 
</P>
<P>
	Nixon, used mainly off the bench as a late-inning defensive  
replacement and pinch runner, was hitting .188 with 18 stolen 
bases. 
  	   	
</P>
