<CATEGORY> international </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Death Toll Rises to 257 in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	GAISAL, India (AP) -- Rescue workers pulled apart a mountain of  
twisted metal today to get to bodies believed trapped in the 
wreckage of two trains that collided head-on in northeastern India. 
At least 257 bodies had been removed. 
</P>
<P>
	At least 50 more people were thought to be inside three smashed  
train cars, and authorities believed none had survived. Officials 
had earlier feared more than 200 people were trapped inside. 
</P>
<P>
	The stench of rotting, charred flesh rose from a field where the  
