<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brister Starts Life After Elway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SYDNEY, Australia (AP) -- He can travel to the end of the earth,  
but he can't escape comparisons with the great John Elway. 
</P>
<P>
	Bubby Brister will lead the Denver Broncos into life after Elway  
in the season's opening exhibition game against San Diego in 
Sydney, Australia, on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	After flying about as far away as possible from Mile High  
Stadium, Brister could be excused for thinking he'd escaped the 
fuss over his rise to starting quarterback. 
</P>
<P>
	And after a brisk practice session Brister tried to convince the  
local media that no-one was comparing him with the quarterback who 
led Denver to the past two Super Bowl victories. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hopefully, no-one's comparing me to John,'' Brister said. ``I  
haven't done anything to deserve to be compared to John Elway. He's 
one of the best that have ever played.'' 
</P>
<P>
	While no-one is suggesting journeyman Brister is in the same  
league, the comparisons are sure to run all season. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've got the opportunity to be a good quarterback on a great  
team,'' said Brister. Last year, he was just that, winning all four 
starts when Elway was missing. It was a major feat for a team which 
had ridden on Elway's arm for 16 years and hadn't won without him 
in nine. 
</P>
<P>
	Brister knows that at 36 his chances of reaching Elway's  
standing in the game are gone. But what a story if he can bring 
home the NFL's first three-peat. 
</P>
<P>
	``Hopefully, I can take us to a third Super Bowl in a row,'' he  
said. ``I'm really just trying not to think about everything 
outside and just concentrate on the things I have to do to execute 
my position.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He said life has changed enormously since moving up into the top  
quarterback spot. 
</P>
<P>
	``I had a feeling it would when John told me he was going to  
retire a while back,'' Brister said. ``I can deal with it for a 
year or two.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Brister needs to make a good start. While there are many  
comparing him to the man who has gone, others will judge him 
against those who are coming, like backups Brian Griese and Chris 
Miller. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
